RIYADH: Saudi Arabia announced two deaths from COVID-19 and 4,652 new infections on Tuesday. Of the new cases, 1,070 were recorded in Riyadh, 971 in Jeddah, 514 in Makkah, 229 in Taif, 214 in Madinah, 187 in Dammam, 171 in Hofuf, and 102 in Al-Khobar. Several other cities recorded less than one hundred new cases each. The total number of recoveries in the Kingdom increased to 549,558 after 2,051 more patients recovered from the virus. A total of 8,897 people have succumbed to the virus in the Kingdom so far. Over 52.9 million doses of a coronavirus vaccine have been administered in the Kingdom to date.